description:
This is a derivative work based created as a collage of clips progressing through a timeline. The clips come from:

The $64,000 Question was an American game show broadcast from 1955 to 1958, which became embroiled in the 1950s quiz show scandals. Contestants answered general knowledge questions, earning money which doubled as the questions became more difficult.
Genre: Game show
Network: CBS

The Cognitive Science Show - John Vervake Channel:  
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLND1JCRq8VujnIBs58kZvrCjdFivR66Cb

Dune (1984) - 
Directed by David Lynch. With Kyle MacLachlan, Virginia Madsen, Francesca Annis

Subs and thumbs mean more than most realize. Thank you for the support.
